.lp
Das
.b Induktionsaxiom
ist Grundlage für Beweistechnik
.b "\[dq]Vollständige Induktion\[dq]" ":"

.XPS "für vollständige Induktion" "Gaußsche Summenformel"

.EQ
sum from k=0 to n k = n(n+1) over 2
.EN

.THS "\*[nospace]" "Vollständige Induktion"

.PS

boxht = 0.3

IA: box wid 0.5 invis "$P(0)$";

box invis wid 0.3 "$and$";

ISS: box invis "$forall n isin NN : ($";

IV: box invis wid 0.5 "$P(n)$";

box invis wid 0.3 "$Rarr$";

IB: box invis wid 0.7 "$P(n + 1)$";

ISE: box invis wid 1.25 "$) Rarr forall n isin NN : P(n)$"

hbbracket(IA.sw, IA.se)

"Induktionsanfang" at IA.s - 0, 0.2;

hbbracket(ISS.sw, ISE.sw + (0.1, 0))

"Induktionsschritt" at IB.s - 0.7, 0.2;

habracket(IV.nw, IV.ne)

"Induktionsvoraussetzung" at IV.n + -0.4, 0.2;

habracket(IB.ne, IB.nw)

"Induktionsbehauptung" at IB.n + 0.1, 0.2;

reset boxht

.PE

.THE

Weiter mit obigem Beispiel:

.u "Induktionsanfang (IA):"

.EQ I
P(0): sum from k=0 to 0 k mark = 0(n+1) over 2
.EN

.EQ I
0 lineup = 0 ~~~~ rarr roman "ok, w.A."
.EN

.u "Induktionsschritt (IS):"

.EQ I
P(n) Rarr P(n + 1)
.EN

.EQ I
roman "IB": sum from k=0 to n+1 k mark = (n+1)(n+2) over 2
~~~~ roman "(ist zu zeigen (z.z.))"
.EN

.EQ I
roman "IS": sum from k=0 to n+1 k lineup = 0 + 1 + 2 + ...
.EN

.EQ I
sum from k=0 to n k + (n + 1) ~~~~ lineup pile { size -3 { roman "IV anwenden für" sum from k=0 to n k } above = } ~~~~ n(n+1) over 2 mul (n+1)
.EN

.lp
Umformen:

.EQ I
n+1 over 2 mul (n + 2) lineup = { (n + 1) mul (n + 2) } over 2 ~~~~ roman "ok, w.A."
.EN

.XPE

.u "Direkter Beweis:"

.PS 3

boxht = 1;

box shaded "grey" wid 4;
"$n$" at last box.w - 0.2, 0;
box wid 1 with.sw at last box.se;

Left: box shaded "grey" wid 3 with .nw at 2nd last box.sw;
"$...$" at last box.w - 0.2, 0;
box wid 2 with.sw at last box.se;

box shaded "grey" wid 2 with .nw at 2nd last box.sw;
"$2$" at last box.w - 0.2, 0;
Right: box wid 3 with.sw at last box.se;

box shaded "grey" wid 1 with .nw at 2nd last box.sw;
"$1$" at last box.w - 0.2, 0;
box wid 4 with.sw at last box.se;

hbbracket(2nd last box.sw - (0, 0.1), last box.se - (0, 0.1))

"$n + 1$" at 1/2 <2nd last box.sw, last box.se> - (0, 0.4);

line from Left up 1 left 2.5;

"$sum from k=0 to n k$" rjust;

line from Right up 1 right 2.5;

"$sum from k=0 to n k$" ljust;

reset boxht;

.PE

Aus Skizze:

.EQ I
2 mul sum from k=0 to n k mark = n mul (n+1)
.EN

.EQ I
Harr sum from k=0 to n k lineup = { n mul (n+1) } over 2
.EN

.XPS "(zusätzlich)" "Vollst. Induktion"

.EQ
P(n): sum from k=0 to n k sup 2 = { n mul (n + 1) mul (2n + 1) } over 6
.EN

.lp
Beweis per vollst. Induktion:

.EQ I
roman "IA": P(0) rarr 0 = 0 roman "ok, w.A."
.EN

.EQ I
roman "IS": P(n) Rarr P(n + 1)
.EN

.EQ I
roman "IB": P(n + 1) rarr sum from k sup 2 = { (n + 1) mul (n + 2) mul (2n + 3) } over 6
.EN

.EQ I
sum from k=0 to n+1 k sup 2 mark = sum from k=0 to n k sup 2 + (n + 1) sup 2
.EN

.EQ I
lineup pile { size -3 { roman "IV anwenden" } above = } ~~~~ { n mul (n + 1) mul (2n + 1) } over 6 + (n + 1) sup 2
.EN

.lp
Umformen:

.EQ I
lineup = { (n + 1) } over 6 (n (2n + 1) + 6 (n + 1))
.EN

.EQ I
lineup = { (n + 1) } over 6 (2 n sup 2 + n + 6n + 6)
.EN

.EQ I
lineup = { (n + 1) } over 6 (2 n sup 2 + 7n + 6)
.EN

.EQ I
lineup = { (n + 1) } over 6 mul (n + 2) (2n + 3) ~~~~ roman "ok"
.EN

.XPE

